 Final Day)</i></b></p><ul><li dir="ltr"><p dir="ltr">9:30 a.m. – Traditiona
 l Passover Morning Services with Yizkor in the Sanctuary</p></li><li dir="l
 tr"><p dir="ltr">8:20 p.m. – Passover ends (enjoy a donut!!)</p></li></ul><
 br><h3 dir="ltr"><b>And on to Shavuot!</b></h3><br><p dir="ltr"><b><i>Tuesd
 ay\, April 22 – Community Happy Hour!</i></b></p><p dir="ltr">It is a custo
 m to study one chapter of Pirkei Avot (Ethics of the Fathers) on each Shabb
 at afternoon between Pesach and Shavuot. Pikrei Avot focuses on lessons of 
 ethics and humility\, which the Rabbis felt would help us to prepare for "r
 eceiving the Torah" on Shavuot!</p><br><p dir="ltr">Join us!</p><p dir="ltr
 ">Saturdays at 1pm</p><p dir="ltr">April 11\, 18 and 25</p><p dir="ltr">May
  2\, 9 and 16</p><br><p dir="ltr"><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/
