BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Magnes": "https://magnes.berkeley.edu/program/gallery-tour-flowing-through-time-and-tradition-april-2026/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:magnes
X-SOURCE:Magnes
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T133000
DTSTAMP:20260326T181045
CREATED:20251008T200422Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251008T200710Z
UID:10001068-1776603600-1776605400@magnes.berkeley.edu
SUMMARY:Gallery Tour | Flowing through Time and Tradition
DESCRIPTION:Stop by the Magnes for a staff-led gallery tour of the new exhibition\, Flowing through Time and Tradition.s \nExploring the theme of water through the holdings of the Magnes Collection\, Flowing through Time and Tradition traces how water flows through and shapes Jewish lives: enacting belief\, sustaining life and communities\, providing the means for spiritual cleansing\, and mapping identities. \nSunday\, April 19\, 2026 | 1:00 – 1:30 pm\nIn person at the Magnes Collection of Jewish Art and Life\, 2121 Allston Way\, Berkeley\, CA \nRSVP\n  \nPlease join us for Women\, Water\, and Care\, our April 19 Beit Midrash Study Session directly following the Gallery Tour from 1:30-3:00pm. Please RSVP for the study session here. \nThe Magnes’s programs and exhibitions are supported by our community. Click here to make a suggested donation of $5 per tour. \nIf you have any questions about accessibility or require accommodations to participate in this event\, please contact us at magnesprograms@berkeley.edu or call us at (510) 643-2526 with as much advance notice as possible. \nAlso on view: An Archive of Archives: Roman Vishniac’s Exhibition History | New York\, 1971-72 and Time Capsules: Exploring the Permanent Collection. \nImage at top: Jonah and the Whale in Haifa Port by Eugene Abeshaus (1939-2008)\, Tel Aviv\, Israel\, 1978. Gift of the artist\, 94.26.3
URL:https://magnes.berkeley.edu/program/gallery-tour-flowing-through-time-and-tradition-april-2026/
LOCATION:Magnes Collection of Jewish Life and Art\, 2121 Allston Way\, Berkeley\, CA\, 94720\, United States
CATEGORIES:Exhibition,Flowing through Time and Tradition,tour
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://magnes.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/Flowing-Gallery-Tour_1600x900.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Magnes Collection of Jewish Art and Life":MAILTO:magnes@berkeley.edu
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Magnes": "https://magnes.berkeley.edu/program/beit-midrash-study-session-women-water-and-care/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:magnes
X-SOURCE:Magnes
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260419T150000
DTSTAMP:20260326T181045
CREATED:20251008T200515Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260203T190036Z
UID:10001067-1776605400-1776610800@magnes.berkeley.edu
SUMMARY:Beit Midrash Study Session | Women\, Water\, and Care
DESCRIPTION:A FLOWING THROUGH TIME AND TRADITION PROGRAM \nReadings and Discussion with Author Elissa Strauss\nJoin us for Women\, Water\, and Care\, the seventh in a series of Beit Midrash Study Sessions inspired by the art and objects on view in Flowing through Time and Tradition. \nSunday\, April 19\, 2026 / 22 Nissan 5786\n1:30 – 3:00 pm\nIn person at the Magnes Collection of Jewish Art and Life\, 2121 Allston Way\, Berkeley\, CA \nRSVP\n  \nWater has always been a medium for domestic work and caregiving. Washing bodies\, preparing food\, and cleaning require procuring and using water. In this Beit Midrash we will examine two stories of biblical matriarchs\, Rebecca and Rachel\, focusing on their relationship with water. We will also incorporate readings on care ethics and care economics to consider the true value of the care provided with and through water. \nPlease join us for a special gallery tour focusing on objects connected to the monthly Beit Midrash theme before each study session from 1:00-1:30pm. Please RSVP for the gallery tour here. \nThe Magnes’s programs and exhibitions are supported by our community. Click here to make a suggested donation of $10 per session or $55 for the full series. \nIf you have any questions about accessibility or require accommodations to participate in this event\, please contact us at dalter@berkeley.edu or call us at (510) 643-2526 with as much advance notice as possible. \nProgram is subject to change. \n\n  \nAbout the guest teacher \nElissa Strauss is a journalist\, essayist and cultural critic who has been writing about the politics and culture of parenting and caregiving for more than fifteen years. Her work appears in publications like the Atlantic\, the New York Times\, Glamour\, ELLE\, and elsewhere\, and she was a former contributing writer at CNN.com and Slate. Her book\, “When You Care: The Unexpected Magic of Caring for Others\,” is out now from Gallery Books. \nIn addition to writing\, she is a curator\, speaker and artistic director of LABA: A Laboratory for Jewish Culture. \nPhoto credit: Laura Turbow Photography \nAbout the series\nBeit Midrash\, meaning a house of study in Hebrew\, is a series of eight creative\, collaborative study sessions inspired by the art and objects on view in Flowing through Time and Tradition. Guided by the curator and guest teachers\, we will engage with texts and artistic expressions to delve deeper into the exhibition objects and themes\, to draw knowledge\, surface reflections\, and pour forth new perspectives. \nAbout the exhibition\nExploring the theme of water through the holdings of the Magnes Collection\, Flowing through Time and Tradition traces how water flows through and shapes Jewish lives: enacting belief\, sustaining life and communities\, providing the means for spiritual cleansing\, and mapping identities. \n\nImage at top: Tancrède Dumas (1830–1905) Egypt – Fellah Women Carrying Water [reproduction]\, Cairo\, Egypt\, 1860–1889. Glass plate slide. Gift of M. Rosengarten\, 79.41.15
URL:https://magnes.berkeley.edu/program/beit-midrash-study-session-women-water-and-care/
LOCATION:Magnes Collection of Jewish Life and Art\, 2121 Allston Way\, Berkeley\, CA\, 94720\, United States
CATEGORIES:Exhibition,Flowing through Time and Tradition,Home Page Event,program series,Study Session
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://magnes.berkeley.edu/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Beit-Midrash_Apr19_1600x900.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Magnes Collection of Jewish Art and Life":MAILTO:magnes@berkeley.edu
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
